                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.002 Mussolini/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-03T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 3, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Embassy’s 9, February 2, 4 p.m. The international aspects of the Butler
                    incident no longer exist. All that remains is for the Navy <pb facs="0763"
                        n="643" xml:id="pg_643"/> Department to take disciplinary action. Therefore,
                    we feel that the request of Prime Minister Mussolini is inappropriate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
